pull_request.title: Add sparkle icon to WebUI component library
pull_request.body:
This PR adds a new `SparkleIcon` component to the WebUI icon library, implementing the sparkle icon design provided in the issue.

## Changes Made

- **Created SparkleIcon component** following the established icon patterns in the codebase
- **Added proper file structure** with `/components/Icon/src/assets/sparkle/` containing:
  - `Small.tsx` - The main icon component with the provided SVG path
  - `index.ts` - Export file for the `SparkleIcon`
- **Updated main assets index** to include the sparkle icon export for automatic library inclusion
- **Added test coverage** to ensure the icon renders without errors
- **Maintained code quality** by following existing TypeScript, ESLint, and Prettier standards

## Implementation Details

The SparkleIcon follows the same patterns as other icons in the library:
- Supports dynamic `size` and `color` props through the `IconColorProp` type
- Uses the `resolveIconColor` utility for consistent theming
- Default size of 24px with 20x20 viewBox matching the provided design
- Exports as `SparkleIcon` for consistent naming conventions

## Visual Result

The sparkle icon is now available in the component library and displays correctly in Storybook:

![SparkleIcon in Storybook](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/43e6ec8e-07cd-4664-8a34-79de4c145607)

The icon appears alphabetically positioned in the icon gallery and can be imported and used like any other icon in the library:

```tsx
import { SparkleIcon } from '@hautechai/webui.icon';

// Usage
<SparkleIcon size={20} color="actions.primary" />
```

Fixes #109.

issue.body:
MMEX version:
 - [ ] 1.7.0
 - [ ] 1.8.0

either in the last stable version of MMEX or on updated development code
(master branch).

Operating System:
 - [ ] Windows
 - [ ] Mac OSX
 - [X] Linux 

# Description of the bug
After upgrading to 1.9.0, I am unable to open the mmex. My machine is on Ubuntu 24.04 and processor is AMD. When I tried to open the Money Manger, it just throws this error message on the screen "random_device: rdrand failed".  After searching in the internet, seems like this will happen only on AMD processor and some problem with Random number generation. 

# Reproduction

Is the bug reproducible? 
 - [x] Always 
 - [ ] Randomly 
 - [ ] Happened only once

Reproduction steps:
In 
Distributor ID:	Ubuntu
Description:	Ubuntu 24.04.2 LTS
Release:	24.04
Codename:	noble

processor      AMD Ryzen 5 5600X 6-Core Processor

Install Money Manager 1.9.0 and Open it.

Expected result:
It should open and show the last opened file

Actual result:
A pop up with error message "random_device: rdrand failed" is coming

# Additional information

If you have a backtrace for a crash or a warning, paste it here.

comment.body:
> Here is the crash file with details.
> 
> [mmes_crash.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/20995366/mmes_crash.txt)

Sorry for the late answer.

From mmes_crash.txt:
"model name	: AMD Ryzen 5 5600X 6-Core Processor"
looks like an old processor (November 2020).

This seems to be a bug with the random number described here:
https://gromacs.bioexcel.eu/t/failing-testes-in-gromacs-2020-6-and-2021-2-with-ryzen9-5950x/2172/2
and here:
https://gcc.gnu.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=100444

The solution seems to be to update the BIOS, see here:
https://github.com/sass/node-sass/issues/3047

Further reading on this bug:
"A modern system needs high-quality pseudo-random numbers for lots of tasks, and the security implications of "random" meaning "always return0xFFFFFFFF" are difficult to predict."
https://arstechnica.com/gadgets/2019/10/how-a-months-old-amd-microcode-bug-destroyed-my-weekend/
One can guess, that this bug has security implications.

@whalley I guess we can close this bug, since MMEX cannot do much here.

issue.title: Pico Display Base Board : keyboard on pico not recognized.
issue.body:
Hi,

I use the latest Pico Display Base Board 1.52 and a 73 TFT LCD 800x480 cran Tactile AVR STM32 Arm SSD1963 (from amazon.com.be).
I use a Raspberry Pi Pico.

At the beginning, the pico is no connected to the Pico Display Base Board.
I use a breadboard.
I put on the pico the picomite firmware PicoMiteRP2040USBV6.00.03.uf2.
5v power is given to the pico using the Vbus (pin 40) and Gnd (pin 38).
I can communicate with mmbasic using the UART on pin GP8 and GP9 like described in the picomite manual page 11.
I can also use the keyboard connected to the micro-usb port of the pico.
Here are the option used :
> option list
PicoMite MMBasic USB RP2040 Edition V6.00.03
OPTION SERIAL CONSOLE COM2,GP8,GP9
OPTION COLOURCODE ON
OPTION KEYBOARD FR, 0, 0, 150, 150
OPTION CPUSPEED (KHz) 200000
OPTION KEYBOARD REPEAT 150,150
>
At this point, I use picocom and a USB-TTL connector the communicate to mmbasic both ways (rx and tx). I can also use the connected keyboard to send commands to mmbasic. I see the results in the sdcreen of picocom.

The aim is to use the Pico Display Base Board.
So I connect the Raspberry Pi Pico to this board and connect the lcdpanel.
OPtion list gives the following : 
> option list
PicoMite MMBasic USB RP2040 Edition V6.00.03
OPTION SERIAL CONSOLE COM2,GP20,GP21
OPTION SYSTEM SPI GP10,GP11,GP12
OPTION SYSTEM I2C GP8,GP9
OPTION COLOURCODE ON
OPTION KEYBOARD FR, 0, 0, 150, 150
OPTION CPUSPEED (KHz) 200000
OPTION LCDPANEL CONSOLE
OPTION DISPLAY 40, 100
OPTION LCDPANEL SSD1963_7, LANDSCAPE
OPTION GUI CONTROLS 75
OPTION TOUCH GP18,GP19
GUI CALIBRATE 0, 3033, 0, 11011, 9223372036854775807
OPTION SDCARD GP22
OPTION KEYBOARD REPEAT 150,150
>

So everything is working good except that the keyboard connected to the pico is not recognized.

How can I resolve this issue ?

Thanks for the collaboration.

toone

Sort the Calculations Tab breakdown lists by value (#7211)

There is already a sort by type, but this is not used for a lot of
breakdowns. Applying a sort by value should make it easier to read the
breakdown without disrupting the sort by type.

* Sort the CalcBreakdownControl taking in consideration boolean values.

Some breakdowns can contain a mix of `number` and `boolean`. e.g. the skill buffs breakdown if you have a golem active will have a `Condition: have golem` with value of `true`.

The values in this kind of breakdown are pretty sparse and sorting them in a coherent way is not easy, so for the sake of this PR we can just keep skip(return false) when comparing number and boolean.

* Use a copy of the modList in CalcBreakdownControl

If we try to sort on the original modlist, we'll actually change the order of the values in memory and next time we sort again, some of the mods can move position.

Using a copy of the table--which will be discarded after use--will prevent this.

pull_request.title: feat: Add audio_classification
pull_request.body:
###  Feat: Add Audio Classification

### Description

This PR implements a complete, memory-efficient audio classification pipeline for real-time inference on ESP32. It successfully processes audio from an I2S microphone, extracts features, and runs a TFLite model to classify audios.



###  **How It Works**

The data flows through a simple, 4-stage pipeline:

1.   **Audio Capture**: Reads `44032` 16-bit PCM samples from an I2S microphone.
2.   **Feature Extraction**: Converts audio to a `9976`-element feature vector (`43 frames  232 features`) .
3.   **Model Inference**: The TFLite engine performs `int8` quantized inference on an embedded model. It internally handles all `float32`  `int8` conversions.
4.   **Results**: Outputs `float32` probabilities for 3 classes: "Background Noise", "one", and "two".



###  **Key Architectural Features**

*   **Modular Design**: Built with standardized `Sensor`, `Processor`, and `Engine` components for easy extension and testing.
*   **Memory-Efficient**: Leverages PSRAM for large buffers (`heap_caps`), employs RAII for automatic cleanup, and minimizes data copies.
*   **Optimized Performance**: Uses **KissFFT** for fast spectral analysis and **Int8 Quantization** for accelerated TFLite inference.
*   **Robust & Safe**: Implements clear `core::Status` error handling and C++ template-based type safety.



###  **Core Components Changed**

*   **`InferencePipeline`**: Orchestrates the entire data flow.
*   **`FeatureExtractor`**: Implements the STFT-based feature generation logic.
*   **`TFLiteEngine`**: Wraps the TFLite Micro interpreter, handling model loading and inference.
*   **`MicrophoneI2S`**: Provides the hardware audio capture interface.
*   **`main.cpp` (Example)**: Demonstrates the end-to-end usage of the pipeline.



###  **Verification**

The full pipeline has been tested on hardware and successfully classifies audio in real-time. The architecture is now stable and ready for further feature development.

issue.body:
## Brave Software staff comment (by @bsclifton)

This is possible already if you visit brave://flags and search for `android-bottom-toolbar` flag and enable. 

We'll be rolling this out when the time is right - stay tuned to this issue for more information  

------------

**Did you search for similar issues before submitting this one?**
Yes

**Description:**
Chromium 66 removed the 'Chrome Home' flag from chrome://flags which gave the user the ability to put URL bar, etc on the bottom of the screen. This was a popular feature and it would be good to get it back if we can.

Requested via community: https://community.brave.com/t/reimplement-bottom-screen-navigation/21529

**Device Details:**
   - Install Type(ARM, x86): all
   - Device(Phone, Tablet, Phablet): all
   - Android Version: all
    
**Brave Version:**
1.0.45+ (chromium 66 was introduced with 1.0.45)

**Steps to reproduce:**
    1. Update to or install 1.0.45 or higher version.
    2. Navigate to chrome://flags
    3. `Chrome Home` option is no longer available.

**Actual Behavior**
Chromium 66 removed this option.

**Expected Behavior**
Would be good if we could have a Brave setting for this as it was a popular feature.

**Is this an issue with Beta build?**
n/a

**Is this an issue in the currently released version?**
yes

**Additional information**
This feature was purposefully dropped in chromium 66 - https://www.androidpolice.com/2018/02/16/experimental-chrome-home-interface-now-chrome-duplex-address-bar-back-top/
